  jobs, custom services, SSRS DPs, ...). It must exist BEFORE those cases run and
  must survive the per-case rollback. See docs/AGENT_EVAL_LOOP.md §4a/§11 and
  eval/fixtures/README.md for the provisioning + rollback-exclusion contract.

  Why it lives here (root cause, eval/ROADMAP.md step 1): the table was
  originally created only as artifact 1 of case L1-form-basic. The implementer
  protocol rolls back every case after scoring, so the shared table could never
  survive — each rollback re-broke every dependent case. Separating the fixture
  from its origin case (this file) is the fix.

  Shape recovered verbatim from the 2026-06-30 golden
  eval/goldens/L1-form-basic/ConDemoNoteHeader.metadata.xml (the golden of the
  table itself), so provisioning reproduces exactly what dependent cases and
  their goldens were captured against. Keep this in sync with that golden: if the
  L1-form-basic table golden changes, this fixture changes with it.

  Name reflects EXTENSION_PREFIX=Con applied to the authored name "DemoNoteHeader"
  — the provisioned AOT object is ConDemoNoteHeader.
-->
